\": \"renewable energy\", \"from\": 3287, \"to\": 3303}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3342}, {\"ngram\": \"support\", \"from\": 3346, \"to\": 3353}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, they seem to have accepted the proposal, as evidenced by their since-invested heavily in renewables.\", \"from\": 3386, \"to\": 3498, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3396}, {\"ngram\": \"the proposal\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3437}, {\"ngram\": \"renewables\", \"from\": 3487, \"to\": 3497}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, with nuclear energy threatening renewables, we see an anti-nuclear campaign being waged, so devoid of reasonable argument that a need has been found to resort to nonsense.\", \"from\": 3500, \"to\": 3676, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nuclear energy\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3524}, {\"ngram\": \"an anti-nuclear campaign\", \"from\": 3556, \"to\": 3580}, {\"ngram\": \"reasonable argument\", \"from\": 3607, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"a need\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3638}, {\"ngram\": \"nonsense\", \"from\": 3667, \"to\": 3675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Simpsons\\\" landing a multi-eyed fish, Homer juggling radioactive material, with a three-eyed koala bear tossed in for good measure.\", \"from\": 3677, \"to\": 3812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3678, \"end\": 3690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Simpsons\", \"score\": 0.9999989614017004, \"rank\": 1.038599425751389e-06, \"text\": \"The Simpsons\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Simpsons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Simpsons\"}, {\"begin\": 3774, \"end\": 3779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koala\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"koala\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koala\"}], \"noun_phrase